sentences: Records label, which released several records from 1988â€“1992 that were club hits in the Baltimore area, as well as in the British rave scene. "Don't Hold Back", "Too Much Energy", and "Let the Freak" were sampled and played heavily by DJs and producers in the Baltimore club scene.
Carter and Aston Harvey of Freestylers formed Blapps Posse, a production team active in the late 1980s and early 1990s.
